li.span: An end user accesses an SAP solution using an application client and creates data that is relevant for

ul.li: SAP Cloud Identity Services handle identity management and authentication allowing secure authentication.

div.div:
For scenarios using SAP Document reporting and Compliance, cloud edition:
An SAP cloud or on-premise solution exchanges data for electronic documents and statuary reports with SAP Document and Reporting Compliance, cloud edition, which handles their exchange centrally for several business scenarios.
In case of SAP on premise solutions SAP Connectivity service is used for selected scenarios. SAP Application Interface Framework can enable integration monitoring and error handling by business users.
When there is a requirement to exchange electronic documents through the Peppol network its Peppol access point connects with Peppol Services to determine metadata of the receiving business partners.
Electronic documents are exchanged with business partners which are members of the Peppol network.
In case of business scenarios that are not based on Peppol the electronic documents are transmitted to the local authority or its designee.
Business user can email correspondence items directly from the SAP solution to the business partner along statuary reports.For scenarios using SAP Integration Suite:
An SAP cloud or on-premise solution exchanges data for electronic documents and statuary reports with the Cloud Integration capability of SAP Integration Suite.
In case of an SAP on-premise solution SAP Connectivity service is used for selected scenarios. SAP Application Interface Framework can enable integration monitoring and error handling by business users.
SAP Business Accelerator Hub provides predefined integration flows and also APIs, adapters and more to build custom integration flows which are deployed on Cloud Integration.
Cloud Integration sends the electronic documents to the tax authorities' or designee’s platform.For scenarios based on manual data exchange:
Manual up and download of formatted files which were generated by SAP solutions through web portals provided by the local authority.
Manual entering of data in the authorities' portal or other local applications/providers.
